            . I am a <rs id="t18230910-316-viclabel1694" type="occupation">journeyman silversmith</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230910-316-victim2709 t18230910-316-viclabel1694"></join>, and live in Monkwell-street. On the 3d of August, about ten o'clock at night, I was passing along <placeName id="t18230910-316-crimeloc1695">Bloomsbury</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18230910-316-crimeloc1695" type="placeName" value="Bloomsbury"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18230910-316-crimeloc1695" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230910-316-off1692 t18230910-316-crimeloc1695"></join>, and heard the cry of Stop thief! I saw somebody running along the other side of the way; Riley brought the prisoner up to me, and said, he had picked my pocket; I then felt, and missed my handkerchief. Riley produced it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18230910-316-person2711">
                  PHILIP 
                  RILEY
               <interp inst="t18230910-316-person2711" type="surname" value="RILEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-316-person2711" type="given" value="PHILIP"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18230910-316-person2711" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a patrol of Bloomsbury. About ten o'clock at night, I saw the prisoner and two others at the corner of George-street, I watched them; the prosecutor and a female went by - they both followed behind; the prisoner stopped down, and took the handkerchief out of his pocket, turned round and ran against me; I seized him, and said,</p>
               <p>"Ned, this won't do;" he immediately dropped it, and I picked it up, and called to the people to stop the prosecutor.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. He laid hold of me, and said I stole the handkerchief - he found it on the ground.</p>
